						               													<description>Bring Guns to Bear (BGB) is a simulation of modern era (WWI &amp;amp; WWII) tactical naval combat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[All game files available below: Rule Book, Player Aids, Ship Database.]&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Simple rules are employed for fast play while still retaining the essence of &amp;lsquo;big gun&amp;rsquo; naval surface engagements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Typically, up to 14 Individual ships may be represented in this hex and counter game (no rulers or protractors). Played by two players in opposition or as a solitaire game using the AI.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Movement by impulse allows reduced footprint and avoids extended range hex counts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Dice rolls are always to some immediate purpose (not just to see what further table to roll on), either 2d6 or (2d6 + 1d6); no buckets of dice!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Separate targeting tables for WWI and WWII.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Ships weakened by damage become progressively more susceptible through reduced damage control capability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Minimal logging requirements using simple strikethrough.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Includes random scenario generator.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All games files are posted with this listing for free use (I retain copyright), and I am open to ongoing design tweak suggestions from the community. I'm also open to approaches from publishers interested in producing a 'deluxe' version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
